<paragraph blockId="8.[173,659,194,879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
margins of pronotum orange to red; sub-basal, middle, and subapical regions of elytral explanate margins orange; sub-basal, postmedian, and subapical areas of disc also orange to red; legs (
<figureCitation box="[564,655,274,295]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[196,1124,191,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-1@1.[190,1133,183,1615]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–12. Convexocoleus rileyi, male: 1) Dorsal view; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral view. C. rileyi, female: 4) Dorsal view; 5) Lateral view; 6) Ventral view. Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata, sex undetermined: 7) Dorsal view; 8) Lateral view; 9) Ventral view. Botanochara impressa, sex undetermined: 10) Dorsal view; 11) Lateral view; 12) Ventral view." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[173,197,300,321]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[175,215,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[151,1171,201,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[151,1172,193,1519]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 14–22. Antennae: 14) Convexocoleus rileyi; 15) Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata; 16) Botanochara impressa. Pretarsal claws, white outline shows the shape of the basal tooth on the pretarsal claw; arrow indicates the connected bases: 17) C. rileyi; 18) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 19) B. impressa. Anterior portion of prosternum, lateral view: 20) C. rileyi; 21) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 22) B. impressa." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">17</figureCitation>
) black with pale brown setae; abdomen (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[196,1124,191,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-1@1.[190,1133,183,1615]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–12. Convexocoleus rileyi, male: 1) Dorsal view; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral view. C. rileyi, female: 4) Dorsal view; 5) Lateral view; 6) Ventral view. Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata, sex undetermined: 7) Dorsal view; 8) Lateral view; 9) Ventral view. Botanochara impressa, sex undetermined: 10) Dorsal view; 11) Lateral view; 12) Ventral view." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
) black with sublateral brown depressions on ventrites II–V.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[173,659,194,879]" lastBlockId="8.[707,1194,194,693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="529">
Antennomere (
<figureCitation box="[355,433,380,401]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[175,215,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[151,1171,201,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[151,1172,193,1519]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 14–22. Antennae: 14) Convexocoleus rileyi; 15) Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata; 16) Botanochara impressa. Pretarsal claws, white outline shows the shape of the basal tooth on the pretarsal claw; arrow indicates the connected bases: 17) C. rileyi; 18) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 19) B. impressa. Anterior portion of prosternum, lateral view: 20) C. rileyi; 21) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 22) B. impressa." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) IV slender, slightly broader apically; antennomere V about 0.8 times as long as antennomere IV, broader apically; antennomeres VI–VIII each as long as antennomere V, broader than antennomere V; antennomeres IX–X quadrate, as long as antennomere V; antennomere XI slightly shorter than antennomere III. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[371,464,566,587]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[196,1124,191,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-1@1.[190,1133,183,1615]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–12. Convexocoleus rileyi, male: 1) Dorsal view; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral view. C. rileyi, female: 4) Dorsal view; 5) Lateral view; 6) Ventral view. Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata, sex undetermined: 7) Dorsal view; 8) Lateral view; 9) Ventral view. Botanochara impressa, sex undetermined: 10) Dorsal view; 11) Lateral view; 12) Ventral view." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Figs. 1, 4</figureCitation>
) hemispherical with disc and anterior margin slightly convex; lateral margin rounded, smoothly curved without angle at posterolateral margin; explanate margin broader posteriorly; basal line broadly rounded; disc distinctly delimited by black coloration and depression between disc and margin; discal surface smooth; lateral marginal area finely and sparsely punctate; ventral surface of anterior margin rugose (
<figureCitation box="[180,252,805,826]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1686,1705]" captionTargetBox="[173,659,969,1663]" captionTargetId="figure-600@8.[172,659,969,1663]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 23. Rugose surface on the anteromedial region of the ventral surface of the pronotum of Convexocoleus rileyi." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[394,490,805,826]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[196,1124,191,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-1@1.[190,1133,183,1615]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–12. Convexocoleus rileyi, male: 1) Dorsal view; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral view. C. rileyi, female: 4) Dorsal view; 5) Lateral view; 6) Ventral view. Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata, sex undetermined: 7) Dorsal view; 8) Lateral view; 9) Ventral view. Botanochara impressa, sex undetermined: 10) Dorsal view; 11) Lateral view; 12) Ventral view." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[502,527,805,826]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[175,215,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[151,1171,201,1518]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[151,1172,193,1519]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 14–22. Antennae: 14) Convexocoleus rileyi; 15) Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata; 16) Botanochara impressa. Pretarsal claws, white outline shows the shape of the basal tooth on the pretarsal claw; arrow indicates the connected bases: 17) C. rileyi; 18) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 19) B. impressa. Anterior portion of prosternum, lateral view: 20) C. rileyi; 21) E. quatuordecimmaculata; 22) B. impressa." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">20</figureCitation>
) with surface irregularly wrinkled; prosternal process slightly swollen, with carved mark on surface. Tarsomere I (
<figureCitation box="[713,800,194,215]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[196,1124,191,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-1@1.[190,1133,183,1615]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–12. Convexocoleus rileyi, male: 1) Dorsal view; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral view. C. rileyi, female: 4) Dorsal view; 5) Lateral view; 6) Ventral view. Elytrogona quatuordecimmaculata, sex undetermined: 7) Dorsal view; 8) Lateral view; 9) Ventral view. Botanochara impressa, sex undetermined: 10) Dorsal view; 11) Lateral view; 12) Ventral view." pageId="8" pageNumber="529">Figs. 1, 6</figureCitation>
) hemispherical; tarsomere II heart-shaped, 2 times as long as tarsomere I; tarsomere III bilobed, as long as broad, 2.5 times as long as tarsomere I; tarsomere IV as long as tarsomere III, 2.5 times as long as tarsomere I.
</paragraph>
